# LACON Writer's Harness — Implementation Plan

> **Derived from:** `Questions.md` answers + codebase audit  
> **Target platform:** Electron + React + TipTap (existing `apps/lacon-desktop`)  
> **North star:** *"The best tool for writing and researching — AI is constrained by structure, not the other way around."*

---

## 1. Product Vision (Synthesized from Q1–Q8)

LACON is a **structured, opinionated writing harness** — not a chat wrapper. The AI is *harnessed* (constrained by Skills and the cognitive loop) so that writers get disciplined, researched, genre-aware output. It is strongly opinionated about what good writing looks like, anti-chatbot by UX proof (not by bashing competitors), and ships as a **free direct-download app** where users bring their own API keys.

**Unique value stack (all must ship together):**
1. **Skill file system** — auto-researched, genre-aware prompt packs
2. **Planner → Generator → Reviewer cognitive loop** — configurable automation depth
3. **Surgical paragraph-level editing** — diff-first, never regenerate blindly
4. **Persistent, auditable Research Log** — cross-session, with citations
5. **Zero-bias isolated project contexts** — no chat history bleed

---

## 2. Architecture Overview

```
apps/lacon-desktop/
  src/
    main/                          ← Electron main process
      agent/                       ← ✅ EXISTS — extend with Writer loop
        orchestrator.ts            ← ✅ EXISTS
        planner.ts                 ← ✅ EXISTS — repurpose for Planner stage
        [NEW] writer-loop.ts       ← Planner→Generator→Reviewer state machine
        [NEW] reviewer.ts          ← Reviewer agent (flag + suggest rewrites)
        [NEW] skill-engine.ts      ← Skill file loader, composer, injector
      tools/
        [NEW] research-tools.ts    ← Web search + file upload tools
        [NEW] skill-research-tool.ts ← Agent-driven skill generation
      services/
        document-service.ts        ← ✅ EXISTS — add snapshot versioning
        [NEW] research-log-service.ts ← Persistent research log (JSON on disk)
        [NEW] skill-service.ts     ← Manage skill library on disk
        [NEW] version-service.ts   ← Milestone snapshot store
      providers/                   ← ✅ EXISTS — all major LLMs covered
    renderer/
      components/
        ModernEditor.tsx           ← ✅ EXISTS — primary editor surface
        [NEW] WriterLoop/          ← Loop control panel (progress, pass counter)
        [NEW] SkillPicker/         ← Select/stack up to 3 Skills
        [NEW] ResearchLog/         ← Sidebar panel: query→sources→usage
        [NEW] VersionHistory/      ← Creative snapshot timeline
        [NEW] DiffViewer/          ← Side-by-side old vs new paragraph
        [NEW] ZenMode/             ← Distraction-free overlay
        [NEW] UploadSource/        ← PDF/DOCX/TXT/slides upload
        [MODIFY] AssistantPanel    ← Integrate loop controls + skill status
    shared/
      [NEW] writer-types.ts        ← WriterSession, Skill, ResearchEntry, Snapshot types
```

### Agent Workspace Folder Structure (hidden from writers)
```
[Project Root]/
  .lacon/                  ← hidden agent folder
    research.md            ← auto-written research log
    [skill-name].skill.md  ← generated skill files
    snapshots/             ← version snapshots (JSON)
  [document].md            ← only file writers see directly
```

---

## 3. Core Data Types (NEW: `shared/writer-types.ts`)

```typescript
// Skill file definition
interface Skill {
  id: string
  name: string
  genre: string                    // "horror", "academic", "essay", etc.
  structuralRules: string[]        // "A horror story needs a tension curve in act 2"
  evaluationRubric?: string[]      // Optional — Reviewer uses these
  examples: string[]               // Best-practice excerpts
  generatedAt: number
  source: 'built-in' | 'user-created' | 'agent-researched'
}

// Writer Loop session
interface WriterSession {
  id: string
  documentId: string
  activeSkills: Skill[]            // Up to 3, with priority order
  wordCountTarget: number          // Soft target (±20% triggers flag)
  automationLevel: 'full-auto' | 'supervised' | 'manual'
  passCount: number                // Current reviewer pass (max 3)
  stage: 'planning' | 'generating' | 'reviewing' | 'complete' | 'paused'
  outline?: Outline
  researchLogId: string
}

// Hierarchical outline
interface Outline {
  sections: {
    id: string
    title: string
    subsections: { id: string; title: string; keyPoints: string[] }[]
  }[]
  approvedByUser: boolean
}

// Research log entry
interface ResearchEntry {
  id: string
  query: string
  sources: { url: string; title: string; excerpt: string }[]
  savedExcerpts: string[]
  usedInSections: string[]         // section IDs
  timestamp: number
}

// Version snapshot
interface DocumentSnapshot {
  id: string
  documentId: string
  label: string                    // "After Planner", "After Pass 2", "User milestone"
  content: unknown                 // TipTap JSON
  wordCount: number
  createdAt: number
}

// Reviewer flag
interface ReviewerFlag {
  paragraphId: string
  type: 'word-count' | 'structure' | 'tone' | 'factual' | 'skill-rubric'
  severity: 'info' | 'warning' | 'error'
  message: string
  suggestedRewrite: string         // AI-generated alternative
  accepted: boolean | null         // null = pending
}
```

---

## 4. Phased Execution Plan

---

### Phase 1 — Foundation: Types, Skill Files, Project Workspace
**Goal:** Lay the data model and file-system contract everything else will build on.

#### Tasks
- [ ] **Create `shared/writer-types.ts`** — All types from Section 3 above.
- [ ] **Create `main/services/skill-service.ts`**
  - Load built-in skills from `resources/skills/` (bundled with app)
  - Load user skills from `[project]/.lacon/skills/`
  - `compositeSkillPrompt(skills: Skill[]): string` — merges up to 3 skills with priority weighting
- [ ] **Create `main/services/research-log-service.ts`**
  - CRUD for `ResearchEntry` stored in `[project]/.lacon/research.md` (Markdown) + `.lacon/research.json` (machine-readable)
  - Cross-session persistence via `fs` module in Electron main process
- [ ] **Create `main/services/version-service.ts`**
  - `createSnapshot(label, content)` → writes to `.lacon/snapshots/[timestamp].json`
  - `listSnapshots(documentId)` → sorted list
  - `restoreSnapshot(id)` → returns TipTap JSON
- [ ] **Bundle 5 built-in Skill files** in `resources/skills/`:
  - `essay.skill.md` — Argumentative essay structure
  - `story.skill.md` — Narrative arc, tension curve, character rules
  - `academic.skill.md` — Thesis/evidence/citation structure
  - `newsletter.skill.md` — Hook, value, CTA flow
  - `script.skill.md` — Scene/action/dialogue formatting
- [ ] **Add IPC channels** in `shared/ipc-schema.ts`:
  - `skill:list`, `skill:get`, `skill:create`, `skill:compose`
  - `research:addEntry`, `research:getLog`, `research:linkToSection`
  - `version:createSnapshot`, `version:listSnapshots`, `version:restore`

#### Acceptance Criteria
- Skills load from disk, compose into a single system prompt string
- Research log round-trips to disk across app restarts
- Snapshots can be created and restored

---

### Phase 2 — Skill Research Agent
**Goal:** Agent auto-researches how to write a genre and generates a `.skill.md` file.

#### Tasks
- [ ] **Create `main/tools/skill-research-tool.ts`**
  - `researchGenre(genre: string): Promise<Skill>` — calls web search → synthesizes rules → writes skill file
  - Uses existing `retrieval-tools.ts` + provider manager
- [ ] **Create `main/agent/skill-engine.ts`**
  - Orchestrates: "user wants to write a horror story" → identify genre → check if skill exists → if not, run research → save skill → return composed prompt
  - Writes all intermediate research to `.lacon/research.md`
- [ ] **`SkillPicker` UI** (renderer component):
  - Library view: built-in skills grid + user skills
  - "Generate Skill" button → shows progress → auto-adds to library
  - Stack selector: drag-and-drop up to 3 skills with priority labels (1st, 2nd, 3rd)
  - Skill card: name, genre, rule count, last updated
- [ ] **Add IPC**: `skill:research` (triggers agent, streams progress back)

#### Acceptance Criteria
- User picks "I want to write a horror story" → agent searches, generates `horror.skill.md`, displays it in library
- Composing 3 skills produces a coherent system prompt with priority blending

---

### Phase 3 — Planner Stage (Outline Generation)
**Goal:** The Planner outputs a hierarchical outline the user approves before generation begins.

#### Tasks
- [ ] **Create `main/agent/writer-loop.ts`** — state machine for the full loop:
  ```
  idle → planning → awaiting-outline-approval → generating → 
  reviewing (up to 3 passes) → awaiting-user → complete
  ```
- [ ] **Extend existing `planner.ts`** with `generateOutline(instruction, skills, researchNotes)`:
  - Returns `Outline` (sections → subsections → key points)
  - Research is a **pre-step** (Q14: research is manual, before the loop)
  - Planner receives: user instruction + active skills + any manually uploaded research
- [ ] **`WriterLoop/OutlineEditor` component** (renderer):
  - Renders the hierarchical outline as an interactive tree
  - User can edit, reorder, delete nodes
  - "Approve Outline" button → triggers generation
  - Planner "wins" if Reviewer later contradicts it (Q12)
- [ ] **Auto-snapshot** on outline approval: label "Before Generation"
- [ ] **Word count target input** in the session setup panel (soft target, ±20% flag)

#### Acceptance Criteria
- Planner generates a structured outline from a user prompt + active skills
- User can edit/approve the outline
- Word count target is stored in the session

---

### Phase 4 — Generator Stage (Section-by-Section Writing)
**Goal:** Generator writes the document section by section, context-aware, within the word target.

#### Tasks
- [ ] **`main/agent/writer-loop.ts`** — `generateSection(sectionId, outline, skills, documentSummary)`:
  - Sends: skill composite prompt + section outline + neighboring paragraph context + document-level summary
  - Receives: markdown → converts to TipTap JSON (use existing `@tiptap/markdown`)
  - Updates document summary after each section (Q23 — rolling summary for continuity)
  - Tracks running word count vs. target
- [ ] **Context window management** (Q35A — auto-truncate/summarize):
  - Rolling document summary maintained in session state
  - If context nears limit: summarize completed sections, keep only recent + current
- [ ] **TipTap inline ghost text** (Q41A) — show generated text as ghost before commit:
  - Use TipTap `Decoration` API to render pending content in muted color
  - "Accept All" / "Reject" buttons in floating toolbar
- [ ] **Progress UI** in AssistantPanel:
  - Section progress bar: "Writing section 2/5..."
  - Token count + estimated cost badge (Q36A)
  - Cancel button
- [ ] **Auto-snapshot** after full generation: label "After Generation Pass 1"

#### Acceptance Criteria
- Generator produces each section in sequence with correct context
- Ghost text appears in editor, user can accept/reject
- Token cost is visible per generation call

---

### Phase 5 — Reviewer Stage + Surgical Editing
**Goal:** Reviewer flags issues; surgical edits apply to individual paragraphs with diff view.

#### Tasks
- [ ] **Create `main/agent/reviewer.ts`**:
  - `reviewDocument(content, session): Promise<ReviewerFlag[]>`
  - Checks: word count delta (>20%), structural compliance vs. skill rubric, tone consistency
  - Returns flags with `suggestedRewrite` per paragraph
  - Max 3 automatic passes; on 4th, pauses and asks user (Q13B)
  - Planner's outline is the authority if structure conflicts (Q12B)
- [ ] **`WriterLoop/ReviewPanel` component**:
  - Flag list with severity icons (info / warning / error)
  - Each flag has: paragraph preview, issue description, suggested rewrite
  - Accept/Reject buttons per flag → accepted rewrites go to DiffViewer
- [ ] **`DiffViewer` component** (Q25B — side-by-side):
  - Left pane: original paragraph (read-only)
  - Right pane: suggested rewrite (editable)
  - Accept / Edit & Accept / Reject actions
  - Accepted changes highlight in editor as `<mark>` for 3 seconds then normalize
- [ ] **Surgical paragraph editing** (Q22B):
  - User selects paragraph → right-click / toolbar → "Fix with AI"
  - Sends: full document + instruction + target paragraph ID
  - Response: full new document → extract target paragraph → show in DiffViewer
  - Does **not** touch other paragraphs
- [ ] **Full document rewrite** as fallback (Q26A):
  - "Rewrite All" button in session panel → creates snapshot → triggers full generation
- [ ] **Auto-snapshot** before each Reviewer pass

#### Acceptance Criteria
- Reviewer flags off-target paragraphs with suggested rewrites
- DiffViewer shows side-by-side with accept/reject
- Surgical "Fix paragraph" isolates changes correctly
- After 3 auto passes, loop pauses for user decision

---

### Phase 6 — Research Log + File Upload + Citations
**Goal:** Full research workflow — web search, file upload, auditable log, citation styles.

#### Tasks
- [ ] **Web research tool** (extend `retrieval-tools.ts`):
  - During generation (auto mode): agent searches → logs all queries + sources automatically
  - High-importance documents (supervised mode): agent proposes search queries → user approves → executes
  - Default = auto; user toggles in session settings
- [ ] **File upload** (Q30A): PDF, DOCX, TXT, slides (PPTX)
  - Electron `dialog.showOpenDialog` → read file → extract text (use `pdf-parse`, `mammoth`, `pptx-to-text`)
  - Extracted text stored as `ResearchEntry` in research log
  - Shown in Research Log panel as "Uploaded: [filename]"
- [ ] **`ResearchLog` panel** (renderer):
  - Timeline view: each entry = query + sources found + excerpts + sections used
  - Click source → open in external browser
  - Knowledge graph mode (Q28C): visual connections between sources and sections
  - Cross-session: persists in `.lacon/research.json`
- [ ] **Citations** (Q31D — user picks style):
  - Citation style picker in document settings: APA, MLA, Chicago, IEEE, Footnotes, Inline links
  - When Generator uses a source → inserts citation in chosen style
  - Citation manager: deduplicate, sort bibliography
- [ ] **Fact-check on demand** (Q33B):
  - "Fact-check this section" button → agent searches claims → returns confidence + sources
  - Flags low-confidence claims in yellow

#### Acceptance Criteria
- Research log persists across sessions, shows full audit trail
- PDF/DOCX upload extracts text and adds to research context
- Citations inserted in user-selected style
- Fact-check surfaces sources for flagged claims

---

### Phase 7 — Version History + Project Isolation + UX Polish
**Goal:** Creative version control, isolated project contexts, Zen mode, and inline completions.

#### Tasks
- [ ] **`VersionHistory` component** (Q24B — creative, not git-scary):
  - Visual timeline: cards with label, date, word count
  - Labels: user can name milestones ("Draft 1 done", "Before rewrite")
  - Auto-labels: "After Planner", "After Generation Pass 1", "After Reviewer Pass 2"
  - Restore: shows DiffViewer between snapshot and current before confirming
  - Stored in `.lacon/snapshots/`
- [ ] **Project isolation** (Q45A — zero bleed):
  - Each project = its own `.lacon/` folder + isolated provider config
  - No cross-project context leaking
  - Session state (active skills, research log, loop state) is per-project
- [ ] **Zen mode** (Q42A):
  - Hides: sidebar, assistant panel, status bar
  - Shows: editor + floating word count
  - Triggered: `F11` or toolbar button
  - Smooth CSS transition
- [ ] **Inline ghost text / accept** (Q41 A+C combined):
  - Ghost text (pale) for AI completions → `Tab` to accept, `Esc` to reject
  - Highlighted blocks for larger suggestions → Accept/Reject toolbar appears inline
- [ ] **Formatting preservation** (Q27C):
  - Generator always outputs Markdown
  - `@tiptap/markdown` parses back to TipTap ProseMirror JSON
  - Existing user formatting preserved in surrounding paragraphs
- [ ] **Keyboard-first** (Q43C — equal keyboard + mouse):
  - All loop actions have keyboard shortcuts documented in tooltip
  - Focus management: Tab moves through Loop stages logically
- [ ] **Automation level per project** (Q9D):
  - Session settings: "Full Auto" / "Supervised" / "Manual" toggle
  - Affects: research approval, reviewer auto-pass count, generation chunk size

#### Acceptance Criteria
- Version timeline shows auto + manual snapshots, restore works
- Zen mode hides all chrome, word count remains
- Ghost text tab-accepts correctly

---

### Phase 8 — Settings, Distribution, Model Strategy
**Goal:** API key management, provider selection, cost tracking, local model support, app packaging.

#### Tasks
- [ ] **Settings page** (extend existing `ProviderSettings.tsx`):
  - API key per provider: encrypted storage (Electron `safeStorage`) + test-connection button (Q47B)
  - Model selector per provider (Q38B — user chooses their model, no suggestions)
  - Local model support: Ollama / LM Studio URL config with disclaimer banner (Q37C)
  - One model per project (Q34B — keep it simple)
- [ ] **Cost tracking** (Q36A):
  - Token count badge: input tokens / output tokens per call
  - Estimated USD cost calculated from provider pricing table
  - Session total: running cost counter in status bar
  - Model pricing table bundled in app (updated manually per release)
- [ ] **Context window guard** (Q35A):
  - Monitor token count before each LLM call
  - Auto-truncate: keep outline + current section + last 2 completed sections + document summary
  - Warn user if summary is being used instead of full context
- [ ] **Privacy** (Q46A — 100% local):
  - No telemetry, no analytics, no server calls except directly to chosen LLM provider
  - User API keys never leave the machine except to the provider's API
- [ ] **Distribution** (Q48A — direct download):
  - `electron-builder` produces `.exe` (Windows), `.dmg` (macOS), `.AppImage` (Linux)
  - Download page (static site) — no app store
  - Manual update only (Q49C): in-app "Check for update" button → opens download page
- [ ] **Pricing** (Q50E — free, BYOK):
  - App is free, no license check, no paywalls
  - Onboarding: "Bring your API key from OpenAI / Anthropic / Gemini / OpenRouter"

#### Acceptance Criteria
- API keys stored encrypted, test-connection works for each provider
- Token cost visible per call and as session total
- App builds as installable package for Windows

