## 5. UX Layout Contract (Q39A — Writer's Desk)

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  [Sidebar]          [Editor — Center]           [AI Panel]      │
│  - Document list    - TipTap editor              - Loop status   │
│  - Skill picker     - Ghost text / highlights    - Reviewer flags│
│  - Research Log     - Inline accept/reject       - Cost badge    │
│  - Version History  - Word count (floating)      - Send / Cancel │
│                                                                   │
│  [Status Bar: word count | tokens | cost | provider | mode]      │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

Zen Mode: only Editor + floating word count visible
AI Panel: toggleable, default visible (Q40C)
```

---

## 6. Skill File Format (`.skill.md`)

```markdown
---
name: Horror Story
genre: horror
version: 1.0
generated_by: agent | user
created_at: 2026-04-27
---

## Structural Rules
- The story must establish dread in Act 1 before the first incident
- Act 2 requires an escalating tension curve with at least one false resolution
- The climax must answer the central fear introduced in Act 1
- Show don't tell: fear through sensory details, not direct statements

## Evaluation Rubric
- [ ] Tension curve present and escalating
- [ ] Protagonist has a clear primal fear
- [ ] Setting contributes to atmosphere
- [ ] Ending delivers consequence, not escape

## Examples
> "The house had been empty for thirty years. Sarah's hand shook as she turned the key..."

## Writing Instructions
When generating, maintain a slow burn in Act 1, accelerate the pacing after the midpoint,
and ensure the final paragraph echoes the opening image.
```

